                <td>New to investing, never seen a crash</td>
                <td>SIP</td>
                <td>Builds discipline, reduces panic selling</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Sold property, large corpus, nervous about markets</td>
                <td>STP over 12-18 months</td>
                <td>Gradual deployment, liquid returns while waiting</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Markets down 25%+ from highs, have cash</td>
                <td>Lumpsum (opportunistic)</td>
                <td>Buying at discount</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Saving for retirement, 20+ years away</td>
                <td>SIP with yearly step-up</td>
                <td>Automatic discipline, grows with income</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>Test your scenarios yourself</h3>
        <p>
          Don't just take our word for it. Plug your actual numbers into both calculators:
